{
  "text": "The challenge for anatomically based determination is that, while necessary for the diagnosis of LSS, it is not sufficient to determine the severity of symptoms which lead a patient to seek treatment [CITATION_1] . The extent of narrowing of the spinal canal correlates poorly with symptom severity, and radiologically significant lumbar spinal stenosis is also found in asymptomatic individuals [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
